The paper discusses the transition of scholarly journal publishing from restricted to open access, which is a topic related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of the current situation in the industry using Porter's five forces model suggests a focus on competition and market dynamics, which could be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyberlaw (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions the role of public research funders and their push for open access, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
